        public java.lang.String getPortGroup()
        The name of this port's group. A port group is a mapping that is configured on a storage system between a collection of ports, a collection of volumes and a collection of hosts that use those volumes. This name is what the storage system uses to identify the port group.

        public java.lang.String getPortNetworkId()
        The network address of the port. When Fibre-Channel (FC) is the transport protocol, the address is a World Wide Name (WWN). If the port is using an IP-based protocol, this is an IP address, or name of the port that a storage system uses to identify the port.
